<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="75" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,980,1943]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1124,1151]" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Description.</emphasis>
Body long and slender, without colour pattern, 
<quantity box="[883,984,1124,1151]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="10.5">10.5 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[1055,1141,1125,1151]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="75" unit="mm" value="0.8">0.8 mm</quantity>
wide, with approximately 64–67 chaetigers. Prostomium semicircular; 4 small reddish eyes in open trapezoidal arrangement. Palps robust, similar in length to prostomium. Median antenna arising between anterior eyes, with 38–40 articles, longer than combined length of prostomium and palps. Lateral antennae shorter than median one, with 20–22 articles. Peristomium dorsally similar in length to subsequent segments (
<figureCitation box="[790,878,1268,1295]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
); dorsal tentacular cirri with about 30–33 articles, slightly longer than median antenna; ventral tentacular cirri with about 15–16 articles, slightly shorter than lateral antennae. Dorsal parapodial cirri long, pointed distally, with well-marked articles; first pair with about 41–44 articles, longer than body width. Midbody dorsal parapodial cirri with a slight alternation in length, about 30–26 articles, slightly thicker than anterior ones. Parapodia conical, distally slightly bilobed; ventral parapodial cirri digitiform, shorter than parapodial lobes. Compound chaetae heterogomph, with one or two dorsalmost chaetae having slender, elongated blades with both teeth similar and usually with rounded space in between, and moderate spines on margin, lightly curved upward (
<figureCitation box="[634,794,1520,1547]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1B, D, F</figureCitation>
); remaining falcigers distinctly shorter, nine on anterior parapodia, progressively diminishing to seven on midbody and six on posterior parapodia, blades bidentate with similar teeth, and moderate to short curved spines on margin (
<figureCitation box="[848,1001,1592,1619]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1B, D, F</figureCitation>
). Blades of falcigers with dorsoventral gradation in length; slender, dorsalmost elongated blades 36 μm long on anterior parapodia, 47 μm on midbody, 42 μm long on posterior parapodia; remaining falcigers 30–23 μm long on anterior parapodia, 26–25 μm on midbody, 26–17 μm long on posterior parapodia. Anterior parapodia with three slender aciculae each, distally rounded (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
), reducing to two in midbody parapodia, one subdistally slightly inflated with small oblique tip (
<figureCitation box="[1279,1365,1736,1763]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
); posterior parapodia with one acicula each, distally bent at almost right angle, with acuminated tip (
<figureCitation box="[1248,1339,1772,1799]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1G</figureCitation>
). Dorsal simple capillary chaetae on posterior parapodia, thin, acute, apparently unidentate (
<figureCitation box="[1090,1180,1808,1835]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1H</figureCitation>
). Ventral simple capillary chaetae bidentate with some short spines on inner margin (
<figureCitation box="[853,929,1844,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1I</figureCitation>
). Pharynx long, through about 8–9 segments; pharyngeal tooth elongated, conical, acute, on anterior margin of pharynx (
<figureCitation box="[998,1088,1880,1907]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1922,1947]" captionTargetBox="[161,1419,190,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[151,1436,181,1902]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Syllis bouvieri, holotype (MNHN 0146); A, anterior end, dorsal view; B, falcigers, anterior body; C, aciculae, anterior body; D, falcigers, midbody; E, aciculae, midbody; F, falcigers, posterior body; G, acicula, posterior parapodium; H, dorsal simple chaeta; I, ventral simple chaeta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3674481" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3674481/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="75">Fig. 1A</figureCitation>
). Proventricle through six segments, with about 30 muscle cell rows.
</paragraph>
